Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pop the chunks onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}(for roasting), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Once hot, add the broccoli and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper then remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}.

Pick the @thyme{5%g} leaves from their stalks.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

When hot, lay the @Serrano ham{65%g} into the pan and fry until crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once crispy, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}. Set aside.

Surround the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} in #cling film{}. Bash with a pan until 2cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with salt and pepper.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Fry chicken until cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh.

Transfer the chicken from the pan and cover to keep warm then return the pan to medium-high heat.

Add the mushrooms and thyme and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour in @creme fraiche{125%g} and @water{100%ml} and bring to the boil.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if it thickens too much.

When everything is ready, plate up each chicken breast.

Serve the broccoli and roast potatoes alongside.

Stir the @truffle oil{1%pack} into the mushroom sauce, then spoon it over the chicken.

Finish by topping with Serrano ham crisp.